description: Number of divisors of n which are not also differences between consecutive divisors (ordered by increasing magnitude) of n.
example: For n=70, divisors={1,2,5,7,10,14,35,70}; differences={1,3,2,3,4,21,35}; the divisors {5,7,10,14,70} are not differences, so a(70)=5.
author: _Labos Elemer_, Apr 24 2001
